      <title>Re: Absolute Neurosis and Dragin Thunder nuke focus are useless</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6125#M6125</link>
      <description>Unmei is quite right when it comes to the average thing.  If your extra damage is based on a random number generator, then the average random number between 1% and 100% is 50%, and 50% of 55% is around 25-29%.  If you want to see the max, you need to nuke probably 200 times or so, however, if you want valid statistical data, you only need as many data points as you need to make a good distribution.  However, since this damage value is random, and most likely pseudo random, the distribution will be uniform, and the amount of data points you have is about right, you might need about 20 more tho to get a valid average.  However, I doubt this is necessary, since the average number you computed is close to the theoretical average, and thus you have further reinforced that they use pseudo random numbers or some close approximation.</description>
